.TH NORN 1 "2026" "norn @PACKAGE_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
norn \- Mainline DHT client and control program for the norn node daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B norn
.RI [ "GLOBAL OPTIONS" ]
.I COMMAND
.RI [ ARGS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B norn
is the command-line front end to the norn stack. It does two distinct jobs:
.IP \(bu 3
direct Mainline DHT operations (BEP-5 / BEP-44) via the
.B bep44
command, plus key generation; and
.IP \(bu 3
a thin IPC client to
.BR nornd (8),
the node daemon that hosts the replicated cluster key-value store and the
fleet key directory. The
.BR node ,
.BR peer ,
.B cluster
and
.B keys
commands talk to a running
.B nornd
over its Unix socket.
.SH COMMANDS
Commands are grouped:
.BR keygen ", " bep44 " (direct DHT), " node " and " peer " (talk to the local"
.BR nornd ), " cluster " (replicated KV), " keys ", and " version .
.SS Key generation
.TP
.B keygen
Generate an Ed25519 keypair and write it to
.I ~/.config/norn/key.pem
(or
.BR --key / NORN_KEY ).
Prints the 32-byte public key, hex-encoded, to standard output. The key file
is created with mode 0600.
.SS Direct DHT (bep44)
.TP
.B bep44 get \fIPUBKEY\fP
Retrieve a mutable BEP-44 record from the DHT addressed by the author's
64-character hex public key
.IR PUBKEY .
Exits 0 and prints the value on a hit; non-zero on miss or no network.
.TP
.B bep44 set \fIVALUE\fP
Publish a signed mutable BEP-44 record to the DHT, addressed by your own public
key. Prints the public key others use to retrieve it. Requires a keypair.
.IP
The flat
.B get
and
.B set
verbs remain as deprecated aliases for
.B bep44 get
and
.BR "bep44 set" .
.SS Node daemon control (node)
.TP
.B node start \fR|\fB restart \fR[\fB--system\fR]
Start or restart the
.BR nornd (8)
service via
.BR systemctl
.RB ( --user
by default;
.B --system
targets the system unit).
.TP
.B node status
Print the local node's status (pid, uptime, DHT node count, cluster role) as a
recfile.
.TP
.B node log \fR[\fB--system\fR] [\fB-n\fR \fILINES\fR] [\fB-f\fR]
Show the daemon's logs via
.BR journalctl .
.TP
.B node public \fR|\fB secret
Print the node's Ed25519 public (or secret) key, hex-encoded.
.SS Remote peers (peer)
.TP
.B peer list
List known peers.
.TP
.B peer connect \fIPUBKEY\fR[@\fIhost\fR:\fIport\fR]
Dial a remote peer over its single UDP port.
.TP
.B peer get \fIPUBKEY\fR[@\fIhost\fR] \fIKEY\fP
Fetch a value from a peer's node-served KV store over a dialed stream.
.TP
.B peer cat \fIPUBKEY\fR[@\fIhost\fR] \fIHASH\fP
Fetch a content-addressed blob from a peer's node-served KV store.
.TP
.B peer keys \fINODEID\fP
Resolve a peer's published SSH and GPG public keys.
.SS Other
.TP
.B version
Print version information and exit.
.SS Cluster KV (via nornd)
.TP
.B cluster put \fIKEY VALUE\fP
Propose a write to the replicated cluster store. On a follower the request is
forwarded to the leader.
.TP
.B cluster get \fIKEY\fP
Read the local replica and print the raw value on standard output.
.TP
.B cluster del \fIKEY\fP
Propose a delete.
.TP
.B cluster cas \fIKEY EXPECT VALUE\fP
Compare-and-swap: write
.I VALUE
only if the current value equals
.IR EXPECT .
.TP
.B cluster watch \fIPREFIX\fP
Stay connected and print a line for every committed change whose key begins
with
.IR PREFIX .
.TP
.B cluster members
Print the cluster members' public keys (hex), one per line.
.TP
.B cluster leader
Print the current leader's public key (hex), or fail if none is known.
.TP
.B cluster status
Print this node's role (leader/follower), the leader, and the member count.
.SS Fleet key directory (via nornd)
.TP
.B keys \fINODEID\fP
Resolve and print a peer's published SSH public-key line and, if present, its
reassembled GPG public key.
.I NODEID
is the peer's 64-character hex node id (its Ed25519/SSH public key).
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-key " " \fIPATH\fP
Key file path. Default
.IR ~/.config/norn/key.pem .
.TP
.BR \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fP
DHT UDP port. Default 6881.
.TP
.BR \-\-timeout " " \fIMS\fP
DHT query timeout in milliseconds. Default 5000.
.TP
.BR \-\-log\-level " " \fILEVEL\fP
One of
.BR debug ,
.BR info ,
.BR warn ,
.BR error .
Default
.BR info .
.TP
.B \-\-read\-only
Read-only DHT mode (BEP-43).
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Show usage and exit 0.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NORN_KEY
Default key file path; overrides
.IR ~/.config/norn/key.pem .
.TP
.B NORN_SOCK
Path to the
.BR nornd (8)
IPC socket used by
.B cluster
and
.BR keys .
If unset, the client tries
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/nornd.sock
then
.IR ~/.config/norn/nornd.sock .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/norn/key.pem
Default Ed25519 keypair, created by
.B keygen
with mode 0600.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/nornd.sock
Default nornd IPC socket.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime error: not found, no leader, nornd unreachable, DHT failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error: unknown command, missing or malformed arguments.
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate a keypair:
.PP
.RS
.EX
$ norn keygen
1b0138d6a0aa9b34c8e7eb2769260dfb04db0985bf7184944916e6d5a94ecd9f
.EE
.RE
.PP
Round-trip a value through the cluster (needs a running nornd):
.PP
.RS
.EX
$ norn cluster put greet hello
OK
$ norn cluster get greet
hello
.EE
.RE
.PP
Resolve a peer's keys:
.PP
.RS
.EX
$ norn keys 1b0138d6...a94ecd9f
ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAA... user@host
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nornd (8),
.BR libnorn (3)
.PP
BEP-5 (DHT Protocol), BEP-43 (Read-Only Nodes), BEP-44 (Mutable/Immutable
Items).
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/nostra124/norn/issues
.SH AUTHOR
The norn development team.
